at.com/reviews/master-maggie/|title=Master Maggie &#124; Film Threat|date=August 14, 2019}}</ref>\n| Himself\n| Short\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''3 Days With Dad''\n| Bob Mills\n|\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Son of the South (film)|Son of the South]]''\n| Grandfather\n| ''Post-production'', Posthumous release \n|-\n| TBA\n| ''Long Day Journey'' \n|\n| ''Post-production'', Posthumous release; Final film role\n|}\n\n===Television films===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n|-\n| 1977\n| ''Bumpers''\n| Ernie Stapp\n|\n|-\n| 1977\n| ''Johnny, We Hardly Knew Ye''\n| Longshoreman\n|\n|-\n| 1977\n| ''[[It Happened at Lakewood Manor]]''\n| Fire Chief\n|\n|-\n| 1978\n| ''[[A Real American Hero (TV movie)|A Real American Hero]]''\n| Buford Pusser\n|\n|-\n| 1978\n| ''[[Ruby and Oswald]]''\n| George Paulsen\n|\n|-\n| 1978\n| ''[[A Death in Canaan]]''\n| Barney Parsons\n|\n|-\n| 1979\n| ''[[Dummy (1979 film)|Dummy]]''\n| Ragoti\n|\n|-\n| 1979\n| ''[[The Jericho Mile]]''\n| Dr. D\n|\n|-\n| 1979\n| ''Silent Victory: The Kitty O'Neil Story''\n| Mr. O'Neil\n|\n|-\n| 1980\n| ''[[A Rumor of War (miniseries)|A Rumor of War]]''\n| Sgt. Ned Coleman\n|\n|-\n| 1980\n| ''The Seduction of Miss Leona''\n| Bliss Dawson\n|\n|-\n| 1981\n| ''[[Skokie (film)|Skokie]]''\n| Chief Arthur Buchanan\n|\n|-\n| 1981\n| ''Fly Away Home''\n| Tim Arnold\n|\n|-\n| 1983\n| ''I Take These Men''\n| Phil Zakarian\n|\n|-\n| 1983\n| ''[[Blood Feud (1983 film)|Blood Feud]]''\n| Edward Grady Partin\n|\n|-\n| 1984\n| ''[[Off Sides (Pigs vs. Freaks)]]''\n| Sgt. Cheever\n|\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''Acceptable Risks''\n| Don Sheppard\n|\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''[[The Lion of Africa]]''\n| Sam Marsh\n|\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''A Father's Revenge''\n| Paul Hobart\n|\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Day One (1989 film)|Day One]]''\n| General [[Leslie Groves]]\n|\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Perfect Witness]]''\n| James Falcon\n|\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[A Killing in a Small Town]]''\n| Ed Reivers\n|\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''Rising Son''\n| Gus Robinson\n|\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Frederick Forsyth Presents#Pride and Extreme Prejudice|Pride and Extreme Prejudice]]''\n| Bruno Morenz\n|\n|-\n| 1991\n| ''[[In Broad Daylight (1991 film)|In Broad Daylight]]''\n| Len Rowan\n|\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[The Diamond Fleece]]''\n| Lt. Merritt Outlaw\n|\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[Teamster Boss: The Jackie Presser Story]]''\n| [[Jackie Presser]]\n|\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[To Catch a Killer]]''\n| John Wayne Gacy\n|\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[The Burden of Proof (miniseries)|The Burden of Proof]]''\n| Dixon Hartnell\n|\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''Deadly Matrimony''\n| Sgt. Jack Reed\n|\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''Foreign Affairs''\n| Chuck Mumpson\n|\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''Prophet of Evil: The Ervil LeBaron Story''\n| Ervil LeBaron\n| Film [Hearst Entertainment INC]\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''Final Appeal''\n| Perry Sundquist\n|\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Jack Reed: Badge of Honor]]''\n| Jack Reed\n|\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Murder in the Heartland]]''\n| John McCarthur\n|\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''Leave of Absence''\n| Sam\n|\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''Midnight Movie''\n| James Boyce\n|\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''Jack Reed: A Search for Justice''\n| Jack Reed\n|\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''Jack Reed: One of Our Own''\n| Jack Reed\n|\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[Shadow of a Doubt (1995 film)|Shadow of a Doubt]]''\n| Charlie Sloan\n|\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''Jack Reed: A Killer Among Us''\n| Jack Reed\n|\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''Jack Reed: Death and Vengeance''\n| Jack Reed\n|\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[A Season in Purgatory#Television adaptation|A Season in Purgatory]]''\n| Gerald Bradley\n|\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''Undue Influence''\n| Paul Madriani\n|\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''Indefensible: The Truth About Edward Brannigan''\n| Eddie Brannigan\n|\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[Voyage of Terror]]''\n| U.S. President\n|\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[Thanks of a Grateful Nation]]''\n| Senator Riegle\n|\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[NetForce (film)|Netforce]]''\n| Lowell Davidson\n|\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Sirens (1999 film)|Sirens]]''\n| Lt. Denby\n|\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Too Rich: The Secret Life of Doris Duke]]''\n| Louis Bromfield\n|\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[Fail Safe (2000 film)|Fail Safe]]''\n| Gen. Bogan\n|\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[Death of a Salesman]]''\n| Willy Loman\n|\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''Warden of Red Rock''\n| Sheriff Church\n|\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Three Blind Mice (2001 film)|Three Blind Mice]]''\n| Matthew Hope\n|\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[A Season on the Brink (film)|A Season on the Brink]]''\n| Bobby Knight\n|\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[The Crooked E: The Unshredded Truth About Enron]]''\n| Mr. Blue\n|\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[The Roman Spring of Mrs. Stone (2003 film)|The Roman Spring of Mrs. Stone]]''\n| Tom Stone\n|\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Category 6: Day of Destruction]]''\n| Andy Goodman\n|\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Our Fathers (film)|Our Fathers]]''\n| Father Dominic Spagnolia\n|\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[The Exonerated]]''\n| Gary Gauger\n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Marco Polo (2007 film)|Marco Polo]]''\n| Kublai Khan\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[The Challenger]]''\n| [[William P. Rogers|Chairman William Rogers]]\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''A Very Merry Toy Store''\n| Joe Haggarty\n|\n|}\n\n===Television series===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n|-\n| 1977\n| ''[[Kojak]]''\n| Peter Connor\n| Episode: \"The Godson\"\n|-\n| 1977\n| ''[[Serpico (TV series)|Serpico]]''\n| Jody\n| Episode: \"Sanctuary\"\n|-\n| 1977\n| ''[[Lanigan's Rabbi]]''\n| Burton Tree\n| Episode: \"Corpse of the Year\"\n|-\n| 1977\n| ''[[Police Woman (TV series)|Police Woman]]''\n| Burrows\n| Episode: \"Shadow of Doubt\"\n|-\n| 1977\n| ''[[Lou Grant (TV series)|Lou Grant]]''\n| Wilson\n| Episode: \"Nazi\"\n|-\n| 1977\n| ''[[M*A*S*H (TV series)|M*A*S*H]]''\n|[[Military Police|M.P.]] Sergeant Ernie Connors\n| Episode: \"Souvenirs\"\n|-\n| 1977\n| ''[[Lucan (TV series)|Lucan]]''\n| Fisher\n| Episode: \"Listen to the Heart Beat\"\n|-\n| 1977\n| ''[[The Fitzpatricks]]''\n| Coach Hatfield\n| Episode: \"Superman\"\n|-\n| 1978\n| ''[[Pearl (miniseries)|Pearl]]''\n| Sgt. Otto Chain\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| 1978\n| ''[[Dallas (1978 TV seri